In julia the syntax


if *condition 1*
  *option 1*
elseif *condition 2*
  *option 2*
else
  *option 3*
end



julia> x = 5
5

julia> y = 11
11

julia> if x > y
           println("$x is greater than $y")
       elseif x < y
           println("$x is less than $y")
       else
           println("$x is equal to $y")
       end
5 is less than 11


For this last block, we could instead use the ternary operator with the syntax

a ? b : c

if a
  b
else
  c
end


(x > y) ? x : y

julia> (x > y) ? x : y
11
